Content guidance
- Keep claims, sources, and conclusions separate.
- Link to primary materials when possible.
- Note uncertainty, limitations, and whether experts align.
- Highlight reasoning patterns that weaken claims.

Deployment steps
- Save the files exactly as shown.
- Put them in a folder, serve with any static server (for example: npx serve).
- Or push to a static host (Netlify, GitHub Pages).
- Add your logo under /assets/logo.svg or update index.html to remove it.

Enhancements
- Add search across case studies.
- Include a shareable evaluation report export (PDF).
- Add accessibility checks and ARIA roles for dynamic sections.
- Include localization files for multiple languages.

SEO suggestions
- Title and meta description already present; add Open Graph tags.
- Use descriptive headings and alt text.
